Consider the Chua circuit given by the following set of equations: 

\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\dot{x} &= \alpha(y - x - f(x)) \\
\dot{y} &= x - y + z \\
\dot{z} &= -\beta y - \gamma z \\
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}

where $\alpha = 15.6$, $\beta = 28$, $\gamma = 1/10$, and 
$$f(x) = 
\begin{cases}
m_1 \cdot x + \frac{1}{2}(\mu_1 - m_1)(|x + 1| - |x - 1|), & \text{if } x < -1, \\
m_2 \cdot x, & \text{if } -1 \leq x \leq 1, \\
m_3 \cdot x + \frac{1}{2}(\mu_3 - m_3)(|x + 1| - |x - 1|), & \text{if } x > 1,
\end{cases}
$$

with $m_1 = -0.7142$, $m_2 = 0.8571$, $m_3 = -0.8571$, $\mu_1 = -0.5$, and $\mu_3 = 0.5$.

Suppose we have initial conditions $x(0) = 0$, $y(0) = 0$, and $z(0) = 0.5$. 

What is the numerical value of $z(10)$? Use a numerical solver of your choice (e.g. Euler's method, Runge-Kutta method) with a step size of 0.01.
